'''Macintyre Art Advisory''' are a London-based art consultancy who were instrumental in organising the Orientalist and Impressionist 
Exhibition 2007, Doha. Held at the Four Seasons Hotel it was the first event of its kind for the region and made works by [[Rudolf Ernst]], [[John Singer Sargent]], [[Edwin Lord Weeks]], [[James Tissot]] and [[Pablo Picasso]] available for public viewing.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artadvisory.co.uk/news-2.html|title=Orientalist and Impressionist Exhibition : Macintyre Art Advisory|work=artadvisory.co.uk}}</ref>

