'''Outsourced document processing''' is a specialised area of [[business process outsourcing]] involving the [[outsourcing]] of [[document processing]], to a third-party [[service provider]] that is a specialist in that area. Document processing involves the conversion of typed and handwritten text on paper-based and electronic documents (e.g. scanned image of a document) into electronic information utilising one of, or a combination of, [[intelligent character recognition]] (ICR), [[optical character recognition]] (OCR) and experienced [[data entry clerk]]s.{{fact|date=September 2017}}

